The paper deals with the application of deep reinforcement learning and evolutionary algorithms to train autonomous traffic agents, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multi-agent learning and distributed decision-making also points towards multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the analysis of traffic patterns and flow control suggests a potential connection to control systems (cs.SY).
